Get started in minutes

Our easy to use RESTful APIs and SDKs enable your team get started with a few lines of code.

Copied!
1import json
2
3from peopledatalabs import PDLPY
4
5client = PDLPY(
6    api_key="YOUR API KEY",
7)
8
9params = {
10    "profile": ["http://linkedin.com/in/seanthorne"],
11    "min_likelihood": 6
12}
13
14json_response = client.person.enrichment(**params).json()
15
16if json_response["status"] == 200:
17    record = json_response["data"]
18
19    print(
20        record["work_email"],
21        record["full_name"],
22        record["job_title"],
23        record["job_company_name"],
24    )
25
26    print("successfully enriched profile with pdl data")
27
28    with open("my_pdl_enrichment.jsonl", "w") as out:
29        out.write(json.dumps(record) + "/n")
30
31else:
32    print("Enrichment unsuccessful. See error and try again.")
33    print("error:", json_response)
